# Flexity Platform Rule

This repository is Flexity.

Flexity is the main target platform:
- FastAPI multi-tenant ERP platform
- universal business modules
- industry templates
- industry packages
- AI foundation
- subscriptions
- audit

Do not treat Flexity as a small app.

Before changing code, always read:
- docs/ai/PRODUCT_ARCHITECTURE.md
- AGENTS.md if present
- relevant module files

Main architectural decisions:

1. Flexity is the only target platform.
2. Trailers is a legacy/reference Flask project and future industry_trailers package.
3. Kindergarten is an industry template/tenant, not a separate Flask app.
4. Consulting is an industry template, not a separate CRM.
5. Universal modules must not be duplicated in industry projects.

Universal modules belong in Flexity:
- auth
- tenants
- RBAC
- module_registry
- subscriptions
- parties
- workflows / CRM
- catalog
- documents
- finance
- accounting
- sales
- inventory
- production
- tax
- HR
- payroll
- data_quality
- learning
- AI
- audit
- integrations

When a task is requested, first classify it as:
- platform core
- universal module
- industry template
- industry package
- legacy/reference analysis

Do not implement before this classification.